<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="4072235">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>You just need to write a custom comparison function, then use something like <a href="http://uk.php.net/usort" rel="noreferrer">usort</a> to do the actual sorting. For example, if the member variable was <code>myVar</code>, you could sort it as follows:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">cmp</span>(<span class="hljs-params"><span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span></span>)
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;myVar == <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;myVar) {
        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-number">0</span>;
    }
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> (<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;myVar &lt; <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;myVar) ? -<span class="hljs-number">1</span> : <span class="hljs-number">1</span>;
}

<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$myArray</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"cmp"</span>);
</code></pre>
    </div>
